"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:2.10.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">2.10.2</span> 標題：小盾、小圓盾（small shield, buckler）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מָגֵן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： magen)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1\">GEN 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:29\">DEU 33:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:8\">JDG 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:21\">2SA 1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:21\">2SA 1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:31\">2SA 22:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:36\">2SA 22:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:17\">1KI 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:17\">1KI 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:26\">1KI 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:27\">1KI 14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:32\">2KI 19:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:18\">1CH 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:16\">2CH 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:16\">2CH 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:9\">2CH 12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:10\">2CH 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:7\">2CH 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:17\">2CH 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:9\">2CH 23:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:14\">2CH 26:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:5\">2CH 32:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:27\">2CH 32:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:10\">NEH 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:26\">JOB 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:7\">JOB 41:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:4\">PSA 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:11\">PSA 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:3\">PSA 18:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:31\">PSA 18:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:36\">PSA 18:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:7\">PSA 28:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:20\">PSA 33:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:2\">PSA 35:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:10\">PSA 47:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:12\">PSA 59:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps76:4\">PSA 76:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:10\">PSA 84:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:12\">PSA 84:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:19\">PSA 89:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:9\">PSA 115:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:10\">PSA 115:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:11\">PSA 115:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:114\">PSA 119:114</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:2\">PSA 144:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:7\">PRO 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:11\">PRO 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:34\">PRO 24:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:5\">PRO 30:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:4\">SNG 4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:5\">ISA 21:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:6\">ISA 22:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:33\">ISA 37:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:3\">JER 46:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:9\">JER 46:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:24\">EZK 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:10\">EZK 27:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:4\">EZK 38:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:5\">EZK 38:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:9\">EZK 39:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:4\">NAM 2:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： עֲגָלָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ‘agalah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:10\">PSA 46:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שֶׁלֶט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： shelet)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:7\">2SA 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:10\">2KI 11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:7\">1CH 18:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:9\">2CH 23:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:4\">SNG 4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:11\">JER 51:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:11\">EZK 27:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שֶׁמֶשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： shemesh)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:12\">PSA 84:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:12\">ISA 54:12</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0387_round_shield.jpg\" alt=\"手持圓盾的士兵（新亞述獵獅淺浮雕，亞述展廊（Assyrian Gallery），大英博物館）。\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">手持圓盾的士兵（新亞述獵獅淺浮雕，亞述展廊（Assyrian Gallery），大英博物館）。 (Gary Todd, British Museum, CC0, Flickr)</figcaption></figure>和大盾一樣，這種盾可以是木製（有時包上皮革）或金屬製成的。小盾的形狀不一，但一般是圓形的。木盾經常會用金屬釘加固或包上金屬片。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.10.1 大盾 (large shield)&lt;REALIA:2.10.1&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.10.1 大盾 (large shield)&lt;REALIA:2.10.1&gt;</a> 。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:21\">2SA 1:21</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:5\">ISA 21:5</a> 提到為盾牌抹油。用皮革包裹的盾需要定期抹油，以防皮革龜裂。抹油也能防止金屬盾生鏽。如果讀者不太理解為何給盾牌抹油，那麼<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:5\">ISA 21:5</a> 的最後一部分可以譯成「準備好盾牌！」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> 類似），或者「握緊盾牌」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 直譯），甚或「拿起武器！」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> 直譯）。</p>\n<p>在很多經文中，特別是在《詩篇》，上帝被比喻為「盾牌」。如果這種比喻可能會被誤解，那麼翻譯者可以採用一個陳述句，把上帝稱為保護者或護衛者；例如，在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1\">GEN 15:1</a> ，原文字面意為「我是你的盾牌」的這個分句可以譯為「我必護衛你」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> ）。在這些情況下，翻譯者也可以擴展譯文；例如，對於<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:3</a> 字面意為「我的盾牌」的希伯來文詞語，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 採用了直譯，然而也可譯為「他像盾牌那樣保護我」（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。這個比喻也出現在以下經文中：<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1\">GEN 15:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:29\">DEU 33:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:31\">2SA 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:36\">2SA 22:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:4\">PSA 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:11\">PSA 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:3\">PSA 18:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:31\">PSA 18:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:36\">PSA 18:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:7\">PSA 28:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:20\">PSA 33:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:12\">PSA 59:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:10\">PSA 84:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:12\">PSA 84:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:19\">PSA 89:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:9\">PSA 115:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:10\">PSA 115:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:11\">PSA 115:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:114\">PSA 119:114</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:2\">PSA 144:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:7\">PRO 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:5\">PRO 30:5</a> 。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:10\">PSA 46:10</a> （《和》46:9）：有些譯本把希伯來文<em>‘agaloth</em> 譯作「戰車」，但大部分學者認為這個詞並不是指「戰車」，而更可能是指「盾牌」。<em>‘Agaloth</em> 一詞和意為「圓形」的希伯來文詞語有關，因此可能是指比較小的圓形盾牌。古代的盾一般是用木頭和皮革製成，經常要塗抹橄欖油，因此很容易燃燒。如果某個文化只知道用金屬製成的盾，建議翻譯者加上註解來說明盾牌為什麼能夠燃燒。</p>\n<p>希伯來文<em>shemesh</em> 一般指「太陽」，另外也有圓形盾牌的意思，作為城牆頂部防禦的一部分（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.19.3 射擊臺、攻城塔 (firing platform, siege tower)&lt;REALIA:2.19.3&gt;</a> 中的插圖）。因此，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:12\">PSA 84:12</a> （《和》84:11）中的短語「太陽和盾牌」是論到兩種盾牌。大多數現代譯本錯誤地保留了「太陽」，但參照<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr> ，該譯本譯作“rampart and shield”（「壁壘和盾牌」）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> 在旁註中加上“bulwark”（「堡壘」）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 譯作“Protector and glorious king”（「保護者和榮耀的王」），用「榮耀的王」來保留「太陽」的含意，但把兩個希伯來文詞語的先後次序顛倒了。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
